<plot>Black Prince is a historical thriller with flashbacks 200 years back to showcase symbolic, or mystic coincidences in glorious and tragic events in the life of the great Russian poet Alexander Pushkin ( Levani Uchaneishvili "Tycoon"). Ray Charles Jr., the son of the legendary US jazz man, is staring as a Hollywood film director. Ray fails to shoot his film in US about Pushkin, then goes to Russia and meets a strikingly beautiful lady from St. Petersburg. A prominent Russian prima ballerina Anastasia Volochkova performs the main role of the lady and Pushkin's wife Natalie.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?073434</url></doc>
